.landing_image
  = image_tag 'voicesLandingPage.png', class: "img-responsive", style: "position:relative"
  .buttons
    = link_to '//itunes.apple.com/us/app/congress-voices/id965692648?mt=8', target: '_blank' do
      = image_tag 'itunes-button.png', id: 'itunes-button', class: "img-responsive"
    = link_to '//play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.johnbogil.voices', id: 'google-play-button', target: '_blank' do
      = image_tag 'google-play-color.png', id: 'google-play-button', class: "img-responsive"

%section#page
  .space
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-10.col-lg-push-1
          %h2#main_message
            One phone call won't change your Congressperson's opinion, but how about ten thousand phone calls?

      .row
        .col-md-10.col-md-push-1
          %p#info
            Everyone should have a voice in their community.

          %p#info
            Voices is currently working with select advocacy groups to change the way group members participate in the policy process. Enabling people to call, tweet, or email their elected officials together in a coordinated action is a far more effective way to lobby government. If you or someone you know belongs to an advocacy group that would like to amplify their message, please reach out to us using the button below.

          %p#info
            We are inspired by the
            = succeed "," do
              %a{:href => "http://www.sopastrike.com/", :target => "_blank"} 2012 protests against SOPA/PIPA
            , and want to enable anybody to start a movement that can change their communities for the better. 
      .row
        .col-md-10.col-md-push-4
          %button#request_button.sqs-system-button.sqs-editable-button{"data-target" => "#myModal", "data-toggle" => "modal", :type => "button"} Request more information
          / Modal
          #myModal.modal.fade{:role => "dialog"}
            .modal-dialog{:style => "width: 50%;"}
              .modal-content{:style => "height: 70%; overflow:scroll;"}
                .modal-header
                  %button.close{"data-dismiss" => "modal", :type => "button"} ×
                .modal-body
                  = render partial: 'homes/form.html.haml'